name: v0.132
body:
# New Features
- Added boolean "True" and "False" values as constants for Goodie Templates (#114)
- Simplified "Words" triggering and improved fallbacks (https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/56)
  - Should solve several small triggering bugs where a partial trigger phrase would fail and not give a chance for any other IAs to trigger 

# Updates
- Small update to README links (https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/118)

name: v0.131
body:
## Updates
- Add `expires 1s` header to Rewrite.pm (#113)
- Updated dist.ini so Travis Builds Pass (#104)

name: v0.129
body: - Increase query max length for handlers (https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/86)

name: v. 0.128
body:
- Add ZCI handling of structured answers.
- Move `caller` attribute from Spice to the more general `IsControllable`

name: v. 0.127
body: - Rewrite: Ignore headers if we have proxy_cache_valid set. [#92](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/92)

name: v0.126
body:
- Improve `html_enc` and `uri_escape` to be more context-aware (https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/91)
- Prevent Spice endpoints from redirecting (https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/88)

name: v. 0.124
body: - Spice endpoints don't return 500 errors anymore. They default to calling the callback function instead so that it fails gracefully. [#78](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/78)

name: v. 0.123
body:
This release adds various Nginx directives for our Spice endpoints.
- Add additional `proxy_set_header`s to strip. [#71](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/71) and [#73](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/73)
- Change `Content-Type` header for endpoints that don't support callback functions. [#74](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/74)
- Fixed errors that have been appearing in multiple machines when the tests are run. [#75](https://github.com/duckduckgo/duckduckgo/pull/75)
